# CONTEXT.md

The project's living dictionary. Defines canonical names for every concept and lists synonyms to avoid. When Claude (or you) uses the wrong word for something, this is where the correction lives.

If you find yourself reaching for a synonym, add it to the avoid-list of the canonical entry instead of letting the synonym leak in.

---

## Universal cool-fse vocabulary

These terms are stable across every cool-fse-based project.

### Block

A Gutenberg block in `blocks/gutenberg/<name>/`. Has four files: `<name>-block.json`, `<name>.php`, `<name>.css`, `<name>.js`. Registered automatically via glob.

_Avoid:_ "component" (overloaded with React component, which doesn't exist in this codebase).

### Wrapper

A `.wrapper.wrapper--default` or `.wrapper.wrapper--small` content-width container, controlled by `get_wrapper_attributes()` and ACF wrapper settings.

_Avoid:_ "container" (CSS-grid term, ambiguous).

### Utility class

A pre-built CSS class from `cool-fse/blocks/global/css/`. Always exhaust these before writing block-level CSS.

_Avoid:_ "helper class" (Tailwind term).

### Custom element

A Web Component defined in `cool-fse/blocks/global/js/custom-elements/` — `<ada-slider>`, `<ada-modal>`, `<animate-on-scroll>`, `<animated-element>`, `<g-map>`, etc.

_Avoid:_ "widget", "shortcode" (different concepts).

### Parent theme

`cool-fse/`. Modifications require explicit approval (pre-approved in plan, or paused mid-build). See `WORKFLOW.md`.

### Child theme

The project-specific theme directory (e.g., `my-site/`). All project work lives here. Mirrors parent paths to override.

### Field group

An ACF field group, defined as JSON in `acf-json/`. **Always** edited via the JSON files directly, never WP Admin.

### ACF JSON

The synced JSON files in `<child-theme>/acf-json/`. Source of truth for ACF field definitions.

### Wrapper attributes

The `get_wrapper_attributes()` helper that applies ACF-controlled wrapper width/padding settings.

### Block attributes

The `get_block_attributes()` helper for the block root element.

### `acf_to_css_var()`

The helper that converts ACF style fields (padding, color, etc.) to inline CSS custom properties on the block root.

### `maybe_get_block_video_background()`

The helper that conditionally outputs a background-video element inside the block root, when the ACF video-bg field is populated.

### `block('...')`

Function used to include a sub-block or component (e.g., `<?php block('gutenberg/main-header/logo') ?>`). Replaces `get_template_part()` and `include`.

### Plan

A markdown file in `.claude/plans/active/` (in flight) or `.claude/plans/done/` (archived). The handoff artifact between phase sessions.

### Lane

The size class of a task — `trivial`, `standard`, or `large`. Set in Ponder. Determines how much process to use.

### Approval gate

A flagged action (parent edit, new CSS, ACF JSON hand-edit, etc.) requiring user confirmation. Pre-approved when listed in the plan; mid-build discovery triggers a pause.

### Forge handoff line

The `**Forge complete <date>.** Ready for Temper.` line at the bottom of a plan after Forge finishes. Required before Temper starts.

### Temper Report

The `## Temper Report` section appended to a plan by the Temper phase. Contains blocking, suggested, nit, and accessibility findings.

